    "answer": "India has a rich and complex history spanning thousands of years. The Indus Valley Civilization, one of the world's earliest urban cultures, flourished in the northwestern part of the subcontinent from around 2500 BCE to 1900 BCE. The Vedic period followed, characterized by the composition of the Vedas and the development of Hinduism. Over the centuries, India saw the rise and fall of numerous empires, including the Maurya Empire under Chandragupta Maurya and the Gupta Empire. The medieval period witnessed the arrival of Islam and the establishment of the Delhi Sultanate, followed by the Mughal Empire. European powers, particularly the British, arrived in the 17th century, eventually leading to colonial rule. India gained independence from British rule on August 15, 1947, after a long struggle for freedom. Since then, the country has emerged as the world's largest democracy and a significant global economic power, while continuing to navigate complex social, political, and cultural challenges.",
